{
  "texts": [
    "A \"step\" in the system corresponds to a clock tick.",
    "In an asynchronous system, there is no global clock.",
    "The agents in the system can run at arbitrary rates relative to each other.",
    "One step for agent one can correspond to an arbitrary number of steps for agent two and vice versa.",
    "(Halpern, 2007) Only a few RL algorithms consider the problem of multiple agents acting asynchronously (e.g., (Wakilpoor et al., 2020; Calvo and Dusparic 2018))."
  ]
}